Key Match Events: Ben Duckett scored an unbeaten 107 off 91 balls
Travis Head took 4 wickets for 28 runs in 6.2 overs
Travis Head was named Player of the Match and Series
England lost their way from 202/2 and collapsed for 309/10
Adam Zampa conceded 44 runs in his first 17 balls but then dismissed Harry Brook
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Brook was named Player of the Summer
Mitchell Marsh, Australia's captain, is happy with the win but wants to introspect
Travis Head praised for his bowling in the death overs
Harry Brook mentioned Ben Duckett's contribution to the team's cause
Travis Head is eager to spend time with family and prepare for the Pakistan series
Miscellaneous Highlights: England targeted 500 at the halfway stage but suffered a dramatic collapse
Australia's opening stand was strong with partnerships of 78, 40, and 47
